rComments: This professor is by far the best one I had so far. He is very easy to understand when teaching, he uses a lot of exemples and stories to make you understand what he is saying. He makes it easy to learn and remember the content of his class. Gives a quiz every week but they are super easy and a good preparation for his exams. Overall just amazing.

Hes a great prof, a lot of opportunity to have an easy A in this class. There are a lot of quizzes during the semester which help raise your grade. The exams are clear and no trick questions. He knows how to explain his class very well. Easy to understand.

Very engaging professor. Powerpoints are clear and easy to study. Gave a lot of mini-quizzes that boost grade. Lectures are interesting and grading criteria is well described. The group project was not as clear as the other evaluations, but it was coordinated by the TA.

Professor Cénat taught this class perfectly! Class content was so interesting and the textbook really did help solidify the information. He was really accommodating with the 24hr quizzes and exams. The expectations for the project were clear and if you started on time and had good group members it was great. I hope I can take another class w/him!

This was an easy A class. Had 10 quizzes, a midterm, a group project and a final. There's also a textbook to read (it was useless, barely any questions from it). All questions/answers in the quizzes/exams are worded the exact same way as the powerpoints, so take notes. He calls out for random people to answer Qs during class, which is not nice.

Jude is a good prof. He conveys the material effectively, but lacks efficiency. He often rambles about his research/ life to relate to the topic, but I find we learn more about him than child development. He puts A LOT of information on his slides which are also posted online. Not a hard course, but a little slow because it is theory based.

Prof Cénat is experienced in this field and knows what he's talking about. I really enjoyed his lectures, they were often class-discussion oriented which allows everyone to learn together and to express their ideas. Textbook is useful, his class is mostly memorizing the slides. Overall enjoyed the class and wasn't too difficult to get a good grade.
